labels.label: Feather
labels.definition: One or more feathers not attached to an organism.

labels.label: Scat
labels.definition: Fecal matter (not owl pellets or other regurgitated matter)

labels.label: Gall
labels.definition: Deformed plant tissue outgrowth caused by a parasitic organism.

labels.label: Track
labels.definition: Impression in ground or snow made by organism.

labels.label: Bone
labels.definition: Predominantly endoskeletal remains. Partial bone exposure in an otherwise intact organism should be labeled "organism".

labels.label: Egg
labels.definition: Whole egg or part of an egg.

labels.label: Hair
labels.definition: Hair that is no longer attached to the organism from which it originated.

labels.label: Leafmine
labels.definition: Evidence of feeding between the dermal layers of a leaf.

labels.label: Construction
labels.definition:
Something created by an animal, made with or excavated from other materials.

Examples of Constructions:
- spider web
- burrow
- nest or hive
- caddisfly larva casing
- egg sac or egg case

Examples of things that are *not* Constructions:
- coral reef
- mollusk shell
- hermit crab shell
- galls

taxon.name: Mephitis mephitis

default_photo.attribution: (c) Jane Dixon, all rights reserved, uploaded by Jane Dixon

taxon.wikipedia_summary: The striped skunk (Mephitis mephitis) is a skunk of the genus Mephitis that is native to southern Canada, the United States and northern Mexico. It is currently listed as least concern by the IUCN on account of its wide range and ability to adapt to human-modified environments.
